caption: They sometimes get the order a bit off, or are a little slow in delivery (mostly because they're so busy), but ALWAYS make up for it and rectify the situation if they do. I will always come back to this JJ's. And the delivery folx are always super!
Sandwich was amazing and was great quick and friendly service.
I often meet people here to talk. There was quick and friendly service. Prices are decent for the quality. Similar to a place in Denver I loved.
Everyone at our table was enjoying everything. I'll return friends next time. This place has a nice atmosphere. I can see why they have so many good reviews.
LOVE THIS PLACE! Friendly and fast!

I've learned to never order here during lunch hours. Orders constantly take over an hour to deliver. Even when I go into the store to order, it can take up to 30 minutes to get my sub. I don't understand how a food chain can be so utterly unprepared for a lunch rush. It would be one thing if they were understaffed one day, but there is a long delivery time literally every time.

Took over an hour to deliver a single sandwich two blocks away, which seems pretty ironic given how much they market themselves as 'freaky fast'.  Google provides this definition for 'freaky': "very odd, strange, or eccentric." I'd say that fits my experience well -- you probably shouldn't bother trying to order from here unless you also have a freaky sense of time.
This restaurant always has friendly and punctual staff, plus they get my order right every time.
The price was more then the display. SMH
Staff was inattentive and this is the slowest Jimmy John's service I've ever had. The sub I got was okay and the staff seemed to be at a standstill while music blared in the background.

I've gone here for lunch at least once a week for almost two years. They are always crazy fast, always get my order right, and are always organized and clean. Just today I communicated the wrong bread type and they made me a new sandwich no questions asked. There is always someone checking with you that you have been helped. Thanks guys for your great service and friendly disposition.

Took over an hour on several occasions. I’m on the same street. I could walk there in a few minutes, so maybe I’ll try that. My food is often not prepared correctly when I order online. This location used to be on it! But now, not so much.

Horrible! I placed an order through the app and for the SECOND STRAIGHT TIME, I received the WRONG order!!! Of course, you’re not going to unwrap your sandwich at the store so by the time I found out, I was already back at my office...obviously, this franchise doesn’t take pride in getting orders right...ridiculous.
This place is overrated, and overpriced. I'll tell y'all about it later. Subway and Quiznos were tastier and cost less. Sometimes people just get swept away in the hype of things.

Ordered a lunch 2 hours ahead for my coworkers and the order was over an hour late. Management did not care and even after asking was unwilling to make it right. A huge waste of my and my companies time. Avoid this location
Friendly Service, downtown by Ga State also used the app, picked my food up in less then 3 minutes. Overall great food great place.

Got a 16” sub to share and thought it’d be good to try a more local place instead of a Subway. But the price felt too much ($14) for what we got, a badly non-evenly made sub with no option to have it toasted, not a good meat/salad ratio. It felt like a very empty sub and we still left hungry. Wish we got a subway!
Love the freshness of the sandwiches.
Fresh, fast, great service!
Freaky fresh food!
I ordered delivery, they didn’t have a driver on call. Went in to get my food, them sandwiches made me sick to my stomach, and they forgot to include my chips in the bag. Will not return.
They won't let you use the bathroom. They won't have my business.

I walked all the way to this place  on a 30 min lunch break to pick up my order I placed online,  and got back to the office just to see that the cheese was never added and I see very clearly that the .99 charge was applied to the order.
Always good food and clean

Eat at Jimmy Johns constantly as I travel across the US.  This has been the worst for experience after I’ve traveled all day.  I’m .1 miles from the location at the home 2 suites.  Took almost an hour to get my subs.  I tracked the order and it said out for delivery half an hour ago.  10 minutes after checking tracking I was called and thought it was ready and was told they are baking bread and it’s gonna be longer.  Freaky fast...more like powerfully slow and unconcerned.  To the owner:  you might want to make a secret order some time from a local hotel and see how that goes yourself.  Ordered at 5:14 on your app, delivered at 6:05pm.

My husband and I ordered 2 subs for dinner. Our first time trying Jimmy John’s. We get home to enjoy our meal and to our horrid surprise, there is a small roach/insect in the wrapping of his sub. We go back to explain the situation and basically get called liars and questioned about why it took an hour to return the location. No, apologies, both employees had hostile defensive demeanors. I don’t understand why they would believe we didn’t want to pay the measly $14 for dinner., really?! We will never visit Jimmy John’s again!
Wow!!! That Turkey and bacon hit the spot. See you soon!!!!

I get the marketing of Jimmy John's being quick service but there has to be a more customer friendly way of doing it. I had 2 orders and while I was ordering the 2nd one they handed me my first one in the middle of my order. Very distracting.  I had 2 people talking to me at the same time because the cashier didn't know the difference between certain subs. I had to get my own bag with multiple subs and side items. This was my first experience there. It was very overwhelming just to order a sandwich. I'll probably stick with Firehouse for the foreseeable future.
Cashier couldnt comprehend receiving $21 for a $10.50-something order. Bread was barely baked. Can only imagine food prep was unsanitary bc it didnt sit well either! AVOID
The absolute best sandwiches and delivery
Always yum
It was clean. The young lady was by herself and was very pleasant. Sandwich was delicious 👌
Great food. Good customer service. Quick service.
Great food. Great atmosphere
Atrociously rude staff member.
Loved it
Friendly staff and spacious location
Lady behind counter messed up my order then got pissed when I pointed out her mistake.
Very overpriced and I got some chips from there which turned out to have a mysterious brown chunk of SOMETHING on it. I didn’t even realize until I finished the chips. Super gross. 😑😑
Got the wrong bread for both our sandwiches. Workers were too busy talking. One of the male workers kept using the "F" word. Won't be going back.

I have a coupon for a free sandwich redeemable at any metro Atlanta location within the expiration date and I was told the GM was refusing to allow the associates to take it. They never even took the time to look at the coupon, just told me their store didn't hand them out. Either the GM in this location can't read our Jimmy John's isn't a reliable company. When there are 3+ other sub places that I saw within a 2 block radius I don't see why they wouldn't adhere to their own marketing.
Nice quick clean service♎😘

This lady name Marquita , I believe she is the store manager. She was very rude. She has no customer service skills at all. This was my first time to Jimmy Johns restaurant and it was the worst experience ever. Hopefully in the future Marquita will learn how to take good care of her Jimmy Johns customer.
Pretty fast making sandwiches.  Outside seating is a plus especially the new street decking.
Great and fast service
Lots of options and a great sandwhich. I had the tuna on french bread.

Unfortunately a bunch of unacceptable young people. Slow, lack effort in the process, and unapologetic about their service. Please do better Jimmy Johns I truly enjoy your sandwich. Bad moment for you!

I am writing the corporate office about this franchise. It is the worst! The young lady lied to me on the phone and said she repeated my order twice. My order is locked in their system and they still manage to get it wrong. I have never experienced such incompetent. Who works there? I will not order there again.
Party platter worked well for a birthday party
Service was mediocre. What do you expect?
Good place for eating

Received quick and courteous service. Food was excellent. Environment was clean excepting some papers and material from what looked like a planogram change or new window stickers being put up before open.
(Translated by Google) Delicious sandwiches for lunch and in between.  (Original) Leckere Sandwiches zum Lunch und auch zwischendurch.
Same quality and speed of any location
Excellent food, excellent service and the price was right .I wish there was one near me

Worst delivery service ever. Placed an order before they opened for delivery, giving plenty of time for on-time delivery. Driver called when he was leaving the store telling me it would be 10-15 min until he arrived. 45 min later I still didn’t have my order. When I called to check in they said the driver had dropped my sandwich, because “sandwiches are heavy and it broke the bag” and had to go back to the store for a new one. Also, he was on a bike and not in a car. Never called to let me know. Finally, after 1.5 hours I received my sandwich and very stale cookie. No apology, no phone call - just a note on the receipt that read “Delay” The only reason I gave them 2 Stars was because my order was correct. Sadly, this is the 2nd time this has happened from this location. I’ll be ordering from Firehouse from now on.
Rude. Slow. Yells at employees. Won’t be returning.
Fast but they have zero Swiss cheese just provolone
In a good location with alot of other Bistros
Decent JJ's... Nothing special or anything. They won't give you the vinegrete or peppers on the side tho which is annoying and silly.
Good and fast service.
Fast service, decent food. Place is fine except when they're blaring music at full blast.
I love the food and the service is always fast.
Food and service were excellent!

For fast service, Jimmy John's can't be beat.  Sometimes the sandwich is ready before I've finished paying.  The quality of the bread is great and the sandwiches are satisfying.  They have a fleet of cyclists for  fast local delivery in heart of downtown Atlanta.
Get a big John, with a chocolate cookie.
It's Customer Appreciate Day and some of the workers are being very rude. They have this day once a year so I'm not understanding her attitude. Other than that I love my Vito sandwich.
Love me some Jimmy John's.  What's there to say.
Great place for a quick bite! This location can be loud at lunch.

Jimmy John's is one of my favorite sub shops. Been eating #9's since college. The subs taste great and I love the fast service. However, I was visiting a local Jimmy John's by my work and decided to stay and eat my sandwich instead of bringing it back to work. As I sat there I noticed the music playing in the background was using very vulgar language. Not sure if that's the image that Jimmy John's wants to promote. All about having fun and great music playing but need to make sure that the music choices aren't using language that can make your patrons feel uncomfortable.  Thanks!
Fastest place to get food, and good sandwiches
When the say freaky fast, they mean it. Quickest spot to get a sandwich, and they have pretty good ones too. Grab a cookie, there delish. They deliver to the downtown area as well.
They make your food super fast
food are gud at Jimmy Jones but de who told my first order was really rude and he was fussing. Then he hand over de call to another person.
Always check your bag before the delivery person leaves to make sure they didn't forget your chips. Also every time I have food delivered I receive ZERO napkins.
The Big Johns was a good one!

I ordered from JJ.  Took 25+ mins to deliver to my office.  Order wasn't complete and was missing my drink.  I then had to spend 30 mins on the phone while they figured out how to give me a credit.  Not cool.
We get our corporate catering here often - beautiful sandwiches and huge, soft, super delicious cookies.
Decently quick, normal Jimmy John's food.
This is one of the very few locations that serves sprouts... I'm n heaven
Horrible service long stir short
Clean and quick!
Im a picky customer. They just got a 100 Good Food Fast Delivery Good Customer Service Order Completely Correct AND YES...Freakishly Fast
This location has horrible customer service. I was only there like 5 mins, and within that time frame I witnessed at least 3 occurrences of bad customer service.
Love quick service and decent quality subs for $5. Very consistent, the same experience and taste every single time.
The quality of the subs are good. They do tend to push you to add cheese with your order so they can charge you as much as possible. They charge you for a water cup even with an order.

Worst Jimmy Johns service in the world. Yelled at us about the bathrooms being for customers only when we walked in to order. Then yelled about giving us the wrong cup size when we paid for a large water. Horrible service. Manager had to come straighten them out, but who keeps people who blow up like this in service?
I love jimmy johns, from the food to the staff, it's quick and very good, for a low price, the turkey and avocado sand which is delish!
Only bicycle delivery ... lame!!!!
Not open late enough. It was only midnight and they were long since closed. I hated it because I got no service because you weren't offering any.
Bad service
Amazing, gets pretty busy around 12:00 just around lunch. The #9 is one of the best sandwiches money can buy.Value is great.
